Bukit Asam, Medco Energi, Indofood: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-03-21T02:00:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/bukit-asam-medco-energi-indofood-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  rose 0.3 percent to 3,494.07.  Coal producers: Power-station coal  prices  at  Australia ’s
Newcastle port, an Asian benchmark, declined 4.9 percent to
$123.29 a metric ton in the week ending March 18, according to
the  globalCOAL NEWC Index .  PT Bumi Resources (BUMI IJ),  Asia ’s largest exporter of
power-station coal, advanced 3.3 percent to 3,100 rupiah and PT
Adaro Energy (ADRO IJ),  Indonesia ’s second-biggest coal
producer, was unchanged at 2,375 rupiah.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures gained as much as 2.3
percent to $103.35 a barrel in after-hours trading in  New York .  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ), Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company, was unchanged at 2,825 rupiah and PT
Benakat Petroleum Energy (BIPI IJ) rose 2.4 percent to 87
rupiah.  PT Indofood Sukses Makmur (INDF IJ): The company’s 2010 net
income rose to 2.95 trillion rupiah ($336 million) from 2.07
trillion rupiah a year earlier, it said in a statement in  Bisnis
Indonesia . That’s compared with a mean profit estimate from 19
analysts in a Bloomberg survey of 2.82 trillion rupiah. Net
income at unit PT Indofood CBP Sukses Makmur (INDF IJ) rose to
1.7 trillion rupiah from 1.08 trillion rupiah a year earlier.  Indofood CBP, Indonesia’s biggest instant noodle maker,
rose 1 percent to 5,000 rupiah and Indofood Sukses, the parent
company, declined 1 percent to 4,850 rupiah.  PT Tambang Batubara Bukit Asam (PTBA IJ): Indonesia’s
state-owned coal producer won a contract to develop a coal-bed
methane block in Sumatra, the nation’s energy ministry said in a
statement. Bukit Asam advanced 0.3 percent to 20,400 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  